I have four more reasons why i love new york city...middle school kids fascination with jinxing the subway cars, straight women playing queer eye hook up in department stores, gay men with i-tunes and air force ones, and NYFD trucks outside fine fare.

On my way to city college today i was sitting on the train with my headphones on when two hispanic boys in catholic shool uniforms and a white girl deck out in punk flava are goofin off by the train doors, next thing you know the train can't leave the station because they have dropped a pen in the groves of the door so the doors keep trying to shut and reopen. so they frantically yet nonchalantly try to kick the pen out of the door way. after about the 8th time of the doors trying to shut an off duty mta worker gets up to remove the pen... just as he reaches for it the penis hit by the doors for the final time and is catapolted out of the train. that 5 minutes wasted in the station was worth the good laugh i had when people stopped glaring at the middle schoolers beside me.

When in H&M looking for an outfit for my little sister i was in line waiting for my plainly gay cashier to check me out when a woman came up to him and said her friend was attracted to him but wasn't sure of his preference. Her friend was a guy and the cashier was inaterested... so i suppose there was a homosexual H&M hook-up today. i feel privaledged to have witnessed this triple H event.

On the train back from H&M a tall and lanky white guy with greasy and curly hair boarded the train. he had his i-pod on alon with spotless white airforce ones, old (and far too short) fish bowl boxers and a neon green knitted net tank top. this mans apperance was not the most surprising, the most surprising was this mans dancing, full out lack-there-of-ass shaking, hippjiggling and limb waving. the grinding on the subway poles was when i had to turn my head a chuckle a bit. This man gets off at my stop and this is where i notice his unmistakable gay strut. and somehow this explains his behavior...

So i make it out of the subway and to my left is a firetruck, I take a moment to look for the emergency. i expected to find someone passed out on the pavement of something but instead i see at least half a firehouse of firefighters in full uniform doing their grocery shopping. not random at all.

so this is why i love the city, entertainment everywhere.

Well I am home. I absolutely loved being at the beach.

I left Sunday evening, the day after Graduation (which still hasn't sunk in.) Sunday we drove half way, stopped in some little town where some of Elizabeth's family stayed and in the morning made it to Myrtle. It rained most of the time we (Kim, Elizabeth from North, Elizabeth's cousin Andria, and I) were there. we shopped, cruised the strip (of course) met up with friends, went to some clubs, hung out on the beach ( i am tan, thank the lord), drank (no, i did not get drunk), had to be rescued from the Bilo in North Myrtle, walked the strip, earned some mardi gras beads, laughed it up, went to a couple house parties, met some really hot guys such as Dave the 21 year old Marine who dances so-so but kisses like whoa, took serious amounts of pictures, mastered how to make jello shooters, swam, watched fireworks, ate... ate a lot, watched ppl get arrested, endured elevator smells, threw drunk ppl out of our hotel room, watched dumbass movies, and just had a good time.

i missed my family, but now that i have seen them im ready to leave again ; ) ~G

The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who have a split personality - cold as ice on the outside but hot as fire in the heart.
In love, you feel the most alive when your partner is patient and never willing to give up on you.
You'd like to your lover to think you are stylish and alluring.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is open. Both of you can talk about everything... no secrets.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred.
In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

Your #1 Match: ENFP

The Inspirer You love being around people, and you are deeply committed to your friends. You are also unconventional, irreverant, and unimpressed by authority and rules. Incredibly perceptive, you can usually sense if someone has hidden motives. You use lots of colorful language and expressions. You're qutie the storyteller! You would make an excellent entrepreneur, politician, or journalist.

Your #2 Match: INFP

The Idealist You are creative with a great imagination, living in your own inner world. Open minded and accepting, you strive for harmony in your important relationships. It takes a long time for people to get to know you. You are hesitant to let people get close. But once you care for someone, you do everything you can to help them grow and develop. You would make an excellent writer, psychologist, or artist.

Your #3 Match: ENFJ

The Giver You strive to maintain harmony in relationships, and usually succeed. Articulate and enthusiastic, you are good at making personal connections. Sometimes you idealize relationships too much - and end up being let down. You find the most energy and comfort in social situations ... where you shine. You would make a good writer, human resources director, or psychologist.

Your #4 Match: ESFP

The Performer You are a natural performer and happiest when you're entertaining others. A great friend, you are generous, fun-loving and optimistic. You love to laugh - and you like almost all people equally. You accept life as it is, and you do your best to make each day fantastic. You would make a good actor, designer, or counselor.

Your #5 Match: INFJ

The Protector You live your life with integrity, originality, vision, and creativity. Independent and stubborn, you rarely stray from your vision - no matter what it is. You are an excellent listener, with almost infinite patience. You have complex, deep feelings, and you take great care to express them. You would make a great photographer, alternative medicine guru, or teacher.

What's Your Personality Type?

Your Birthdate: September 9
Your birth on the 9th day of the month adds a tone of idealism and humanitarianism to your nature. You become one who can work easily with people because you are broadminded, tolerant and generous. You are ever sensitive to others' needs and feelings, and you are very sympathetic and compassionate. Your feelings run deep and you often find yourself in dramatically charged situations. This 9 energy always tends to give more that it gets.

the night started out okay but Dennis* is way to insecure around his classmates. dinner good, in the car good, actually at Prom bad. luckily i had a youth group meeting today and it inspired me. one thing mentioned was complaining and how it prevents you from furthering yourself. so i'll stop complaining abt this b/c he tried. but i have to say, i was desperately wishing i was with someone else. oh, one plus to the night was that i got to see certain ppl that i havent seen in forever, like Josh Powell. we ended up having dinner with him and his date and another couple. that took it back to middle school. 

i need to go to sleep now b/c again, i have a headache and i am just a little pissed off and very dissapointed.

one word...

Confidence

if you ain't got it, fake it

xxx

what happened.

27 school days left and i am totally drained, i have to choose a school, i hate classes, im frustrated with what i dont know, BUT the weather has been absolutely gorgeous.

oh, but today i went to dinner with my aunt and cousins (instead of study for Cal as i needed to be doing) and my aunt totally busted my bubble. she wants me to be a pre-med major and i dont fucking well want to do that. everyone has always planned for me to be a doctor (except my mom who tries not to influence my decisions in this) and now that i am showing an interest in something other than medicine ppl are trying to "persuade" me otherwise. i never said i wont go to medical school ever, i just want to study what most interests me and damn, shoot me for trying to persue something i would love doing all of my life. add to my shitty mood. andyhow, im ready to stop ranting now

Step One


Make a post (public, friends locked, filtered...whatever you're comfortable with) to your LJ. The post should contain your list of 10 holiday wishes. The wishes can be anything at all, from simple and fandom-related ("I'd love a Snape/Hermione icon that's just for me") to medium ("I wish for _____ on DVD") to really big ("All I want for Christmas is a new car/computer/house/TV.") The important thing is, make sure these wishes are things you really, truly want.


If you wish for real life things (not fics or icons), make sure you include some sort of contact info in your post, whether it's your address or just your email address where Santa (or one of his elves) could get in touch with you.


Also, make sure you post some version of these guidelines in your LJ, or link to this post (it'll be public) so that the holiday joy will spread.


Step Two


Surf around your friendslist (or friendsfriends, or just random journals) to see who has posted their list. And now here's the important part:


If you see a wish you can grant, and it's in your heart to do so, make someone's wish come true. Sometimes someone's trash is another's treasure, and if you have a leather jacket you don't want or a gift certificate you won't use--or even know where you could get someone's dream purebred Basset Hound for free--do it.


You needn't spend money on these wishes unless you want to. The point isn't to put people out, it's to provide everyone a chance to be someone else's holiday elf--to spread the joy. Gifts can be made anonymously or not--it's your call.


There are no rules with this project, no guarantees, and no strings attached. Just...wish, and it might come true. Give and you might receive. And you'll have the joy of knowing you made someone's holiday special.

 

So my x-mas list:

1. World Peace

2. A replay of November 2nd with all of the Republicans somehow forgetting to vote.

3. A New Year Format for this lj

4. Acceptance letters in March and April

5. My Story of the Year cd from a Mr. Anthony Joseph

6. A decent gift idea for my mother (she does not want another collectible nutcracker, i know i am lame)

7. SnOw

8. more time

to be continued...

good luck on exams all. kisses.

Gina

I love Thanksgiving... i don't think i've mentioned this before. 

This yr i intended to make dessert (cheese cake.) i ended up doing the entire dinner excluding what our guests brought and the Turkey. (there is no way Gina is about to handle raw meat if she does not have to.) 

I made candied yams, some absolutely awesome mashed potatoes (if i do say so myself, which i do), collard greens (that I, one who refuses to eat anything healthy/green, ate), pumpkin bread, hickory beans, stuffing, cranberry sauce, mac and cheese, rolls, gravy, coockies, and finally the cheesecake. it was awesomeness. 

I woke up this morning at abt 10 when my cousin called and woke me up... the turkey was already done... and i was somehow compelled to cook. there you have it. i was supposed to go to our big family dinner with all teh extended family, but didnt get around to it. Apparently it was a memorable dinner with some serious drama; who knew my family had it in them?

My buddy Niea came down from Raleigh with her fam, they've just left our house, so Turkey day has ended. Ive known Niea since before i can remember and it was so nice spending time with her. we've got to do that more often.

well, ive got 3 days to catch up on hw and such things. do me a favor and distract, it will be appreciated.

peace love and happiness to ya all,
~G
